00:17:37.755 --> 00:17:40.461
Well. fraternizing with our
navigator. for starters.

254
00:17:40.496 --> 00:17:41.972
What?

255
00:17:42.451 --> 00:17:44.777
Look. people like you.

256
00:17:44.812 --> 00:17:46.842
You get things done.
and you're gonna make a good XO.

257
00:17:46.866 --> 00:17:48.341
You got me pegged
wrong. Captain.

258
00:17:48.376 --> 00:17:51.380
Captain's never wrong.
First lesson. free.

259
00:17:51.446 --> 00:17:55.142
You've been on the Cant five years now.
Turned down two transfers.

260
00:17:55.205 --> 00:17:57.712
Face it. this is your home.
It's your family.

261
00:17:57.806 --> 00:17:58.961
Is this where we hug?

262
00:17:59.039 --> 00:18:00.573
So. why haven't you moved
on. then?

263
00:18:00.626 --> 00:18:03.012
Because no one tried to
push an XO badge on me.

264
00:18:03.047 --> 00:18:04.342
I like things the way they are.

265
00:18:04.377 --> 00:18:05.708
Evolve or die.

266
00:18:05.742 --> 00:18:07.567
Then at least I'll die grinning.

267
00:18:07.617 --> 00:18:09.705
Don't be stupid.
One of these days.

268
00:18:09.740 --> 00:18:12.406
Earth and Mars are gonna bury the
hatchet and hammer out a treaty.

269
00:18:12.441 --> 00:18:14.497
Yeah. and now you're
dreamin'. Cap.

270
00:18:14.532 --> 00:18:16.343
I'm a man of great vision.
You'll see.

271
00:18:16.378 --> 00:18:18.360
Means we'll finally get out
of the ice-hauling business

272
00:18:18.384 --> 00:18:20.569
and into the
Earth-Mars business.

273
00:18:20.624 --> 00:18:23.321
Less risk. way better reward.

274
00:18:23.545 --> 00:18:25.510
Maybe a chance to
see Earth again.

275
00:18:25.550 --> 00:18:27.758
What makes you think I
wanna see Earth again?

276
00:18:27.793 --> 00:18:29.604
You a "wanted man"
back in Montana?

277
00:18:29.639 --> 00:18:30.949
Maybe I am.

278
00:18:30.984 --> 00:18:33.072
Someday you'll
tell me that story.

279
00:18:33.107 --> 00:18:36.694
Right after you tell me
the story about those.

280
00:18:36.787 --> 00:18:40.147
Well. those are. uh. mine.

281
00:18:40.294 --> 00:18:42.692
It's just... There's...

282
00:18:43.150 --> 00:18:44.564
I don't care about your past.

283
00:18:44.599 --> 00:18:46.389
Everybody on the Cant is
hiding from something.

284
00:18:46.413 --> 00:18:48.061
Yeah. I appreciate the
offer. Cap.

285
00:18:48.143 --> 00:18:51.895
Hey. boss. we need you out here.
You gotta see this.

286
00:18:52.433 --> 00:18:54.295
Hang on to this for
a couple of days.

287
00:18:54.330 --> 00:18:56.328
It might feel good
in the pocket.

288
00:19:02.970 --> 00:19:04.886
Picked up a Mayday.

289
00:19:04.921 --> 00:19:07.759
Looks like a light freighter.
Calls itself the Scopuli.

290
00:19:07.794 --> 00:19:09.119
Anyone else in the vicinity?

291
00:19:09.154 --> 00:19:12.405
No siree. Bob. we are the only
ship in three million clicks.

292
00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:14.098
- Of course we are.
- Got it.

293
00:19:14.219 --> 00:19:17.550
Next to a charted.
non-Belt asteroid.

294
00:19:17.585 --> 00:19:20.045
What the hell were they
doing way out there?

295
00:19:20.080 --> 00:19:21.903
We're obligated to check it out.

296
00:19:21.938 --> 00:19:24.510
I'm well aware of the statute. Ms.
Nygaard.

297
00:19:30.943 --> 00:19:32.139
It's pirate bait.

298
00:19:32.174 --> 00:19:34.514
That far outside
the shipping lanes?

299
00:19:34.549 --> 00:19:38.358
It's not far out of our way. Captain.
Two days at most.

300
00:19:40.824 --> 00:19:43.751
A delay means we lose
our berth at Ceres.

301
00:19:45.451 --> 00:19:47.847
Kiss our on-time bonus goodbye.

302
00:19:48.796 --> 00:19:52.320
I say we move on and let the
good god Darwin sort it out.

303
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:56.658
What goes around comes around.

304
00:19:56.754 --> 00:19:59.337
One of these days.
it's gonna be us stranded out there.

305
00:20:03.309 --> 00:20:05.614
Captain gave an order. people.

306
00:20:05.990 --> 00:20:09.332
Purge the logs.
We never received that signal.

307
00:20:10.239 --> 00:20:12.238
Set the watch and proceed.

308
00:20:17.557 --> 00:20:19.522
See. you're a natural.

309
00:20:19.989 --> 00:20:22.381
That was some real
XO shit in there.

310
00:20:22.508 --> 00:20:26.690
No. That was me wanting to
get to Ceres worse than you.

311
00:20:32.887 --> 00:20:34.392
_

312
00:20:34.434 --> 00:20:35.752
_

313
00:20:43.835 --> 00:20:46.610
Thanks for backing me up
on that distress call.

314
00:20:46.832 --> 00:20:49.382
McDowell's got a
nose for trouble.

315
00:20:49.455 --> 00:20:51.680
He's been doing this a
while longer than we have.

316
00:20:51.715 --> 00:20:54.809
I guess you really are
sucking up for that XO badge.

317
00:20:54.886 --> 00:20:56.141
Turned him down flat.

318
00:20:56.176 --> 00:20:58.141
You kidding me?

319
00:20:58.271 --> 00:21:00.405
You'd be on the short
path to Captain.

320
00:21:00.473 --> 00:21:02.438
Exactly.

321
00:21:02.535 --> 00:21:06.971
Besides. if I took it.
we'd have to stop seeing each other.

322
00:21:07.758 --> 00:21:09.561
Well. You know.

323
00:21:09.632 --> 00:21:12.630
There's that saying
about all good things.

324
00:21:16.245 --> 00:21:19.835
I told you. A couple more
rotations and I'd be moving on.

325
00:21:20.457 --> 00:21:22.578
A couple is...

326
00:21:22.613 --> 00:21:25.910
You know. two at least.
I assumed.

327
00:21:25.987 --> 00:21:27.591
Hey.

328
00:21:27.794 --> 00:21:30.133
There's right now
and there's later.

329
00:21:30.329 --> 00:21:31.853
Why worry about later. right?

330
00:21:31.927 --> 00:21:33.321
Right.

331
00:21:34.716 --> 00:21:37.073
Come on. Jim. Lie down.

332
00:21:38.002 --> 00:21:42.109
I promise I won't
lay a finger on you.

333
00:21:53.152 --> 00:21:55.223
I can't sleep. I'll take over.

334
00:21:56.489 --> 00:21:57.787
I'll buy you a bottle on Ceres.

335
00:21:57.822 --> 00:22:00.820
I'll settle for a
good cup of coffee.

336
00:22:42.584 --> 00:22:43.584
_

337
00:22:43.612 --> 00:22:45.427
_

338
00:22:45.462 --> 00:22:47.029
_

339
00:22:50.664 --> 00:22:53.666
_

340
00:23:10.088 --> 00:23:12.605
Please help me.

341
00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:15.275
Is anybody there? Please.

342
00:23:28.460 --> 00:23:30.357
Please help me.

343
00:23:40.282 --> 00:23:42.762
_

344
00:23:54.308 --> 00:23:55.681
Hey!

345
00:23:57.590 --> 00:23:59.177
How many times have I told you?

346
00:23:59.212 --> 00:24:01.370
This calls for tickling!

347
00:24:01.500 --> 00:24:03.139
No!

348
00:24:03.174 --> 00:24:06.971
No. please. no!

349
00:24:07.833 --> 00:24:09.599
He'll wet himself if
you're not careful.

350
00:24:09.634 --> 00:24:12.689
That's the advantage
of being a grandparent.

351
00:24:12.724 --> 00:24:14.819
I get to hand him
off to his mother.

352
00:24:23.227 --> 00:24:26.278
Amma. do you have to go?

353
00:24:26.388 --> 00:24:28.442
Yes. I do. I'm sorry.

354
00:24:28.534 --> 00:24:30.376
There's someone I
need to talk to.

355
00:24:30.411 --> 00:24:32.430
Are people fighting again?

356
00:24:32.634 --> 00:24:34.379
Not yet.

357
00:24:35.032 --> 00:24:38.561
That's why we need to
talk. and tell the truth.

358
00:24:41.294 --> 00:24:43.591
When people don't
tell the truth.

359
00:24:43.699 --> 00:24:46.109
it always ends badly.

360
00:24:57.258 --> 00:25:01.054
_

361
00:25:02.410 --> 00:25:05.197
You've been linked to a
radical faction of the OPA.

362
00:25:05.330 --> 00:25:07.150
Were you just a courier?

363
00:25:09.833 --> 00:25:11.840
_ - How long has he
been out of the tank?

364
00:25:11.930 --> 00:25:13.488
Ten hours.

365
00:25:19.616 --> 00:25:23.127
I'm sorry the gravity
of a real planet hurts.

366
00:25:23.162 --> 00:25:25.266
But it's appropriate.

367
00:25:25.340 --> 00:25:27.481
You wish to hurt Earth.

368
00:25:27.650 --> 00:25:31.817
The Earth that is now crushing
your weak Belter lungs.

369
00:25:31.852 --> 00:25:35.043
and your fragile Belter bones.

370
00:25:35.629 --> 00:25:39.420
All you have to do to
make it stop is talk.

371
00:25:40.422 --> 00:25:42.475
You're an OPA terrorist.

372
00:25:42.554 --> 00:25:45.767
You were carrying contraband
stealth technology.

373
00:25:45.991 --> 00:25:47.990
What was it for?

374
00:25:51.130 --> 00:25:55.706
A whisper will do.
if that's all you can manage.

375
00:25:56.845 --> 00:25:58.844
Hey.

376
00:26:03.202 --> 00:26:05.531
Give him another 10 hours.

377
00:26:06.744 --> 00:26:09.048
If he survives. call me.

378
00:26:19.573 --> 00:26:22.549
Now arriving.
Medina Exchange District.

379
00:26:27.143 --> 00:26:28.730
Everybody calm down. all right!

380
00:26:28.765 --> 00:26:29.695
Back away.

381
00:26:29.730 --> 00:26:31.452
Back up. people!

382
00:26:41.621 --> 00:26:43.241
Hey! Back up. buddy.

383
00:26:43.276 --> 00:26:44.984
I'm talking to you!

384
00:26:45.385 --> 00:26:46.337
What's up. doll?

385
00:26:46.372 --> 00:26:47.972
Cheap-ass air
filters crapped out.

386
00:26:48.007 --> 00:26:49.269
Second time this month.

387
00:26:51.871 --> 00:26:55.135
I guess this guy pays well
to be taken care of. huh?

388
00:26:55.710 --> 00:26:58.769
Yeah. he pays our bosses pretty
well. too. pal.

389
00:26:58.878 --> 00:27:02.198
Look. don't try to save the
whole station on your first day.

390
00:27:02.262 --> 00:27:03.819
Pace yourself.

391
00:27:06.838 --> 00:27:08.320
Any rain yet?

392
00:27:11.421 --> 00:27:14.484
That distress call
we never received.

393
00:27:14.519 --> 00:27:16.757
it was logged with HQ.

394
00:27:16.835 --> 00:27:19.869
By some anonymous.
piece-o'-shit do-gooder aboard this ship.

395
00:27:19.904 --> 00:27:21.342
Well.
at least somebody has a soul.

396
00:27:21.377 --> 00:27:22.715
I swear. I find the rat...

397
00:27:22.750 --> 00:27:24.809
Quit lookin' at me. Byers.
or I'll put your lights out.

398
00:27:24.833 --> 00:27:26.088
Any ol' time. girl.

399
00:27:26.123 --> 00:27:29.835
Now. we're forced to divert.
or the firm's legally on the hook.

400
00:27:29.921 --> 00:27:31.371
Holden.

401
00:27:31.619 --> 00:27:34.365
You'll head up this
rescue. or salvage.

402
00:27:34.412 --> 00:27:36.377
whatever we're calling it.

403
00:27:36.414 --> 00:27:38.588
Put a shuttle team together.

404
00:27:41.532 --> 00:27:43.143
Is there a problem. XO?

405
00:27:43.251 --> 00:27:46.207
Acting XO. sir.

406
00:27:50.998 --> 00:27:52.986
I ain't goin'. No way. no how.

407
00:27:53.021 --> 00:27:54.895
Well. you ain't invited.

408
00:27:54.930 --> 00:27:57.037
Alex. ping the beacon
that we're on our way

409
00:27:57.072 --> 00:27:59.061
and let Ceres know that
we're gonna be late.

410
00:27:59.096 --> 00:28:00.260
Ms. Nygaard?

411
00:28:00.295 --> 00:28:01.891
If we flip right now
and burn like hell.

412
00:28:01.915 --> 00:28:04.045
I can get us within
50.000 clicks.

413
00:28:04.080 --> 00:28:06.284
Oh. great. Then we'll all be
puking in our crash-couches

414
00:28:06.319 --> 00:28:08.396
while the cargo busts loose
and scuttles the ship.

415
00:28:08.431 --> 00:28:10.526
Make sure that ice stays put.

416
00:28:10.561 --> 00:28:13.355
Naomi. How's the Knight looking?

417
00:28:13.421 --> 00:28:15.792
She's one leaky lifeboat.

418
00:28:15.827 --> 00:28:18.488
She should be able to manage
50.000 clicks of vacuum.

419
00:28:18.547 --> 00:28:20.341
All right. then you're on board.

420
00:28:25.441 --> 00:28:27.061
This is Holden.

421
00:28:27.145 --> 00:28:32.108
We've logged a distress
call near CA-2216862.

422
00:28:32.174 --> 00:28:34.630
We're obliged to change
our course and respond.

423
00:28:34.665 --> 00:28:37.247
Make sure your acceleration
drug dispensers are full.

424
00:28:37.282 --> 00:28:40.980
This will be a high-G maneuver.
Prepare for flip and burn.

425
00:28:56.647 --> 00:28:58.751
Here comes the juice.

426
00:30:31.152 --> 00:30:35.049
I can't figure out why Cap would put
you in charge of this little excursion.

427
00:30:35.176 --> 00:30:36.741
Well. he still thinks
he's grooming me

428
00:30:36.776 --> 00:30:38.317
for bigger things.

429
00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:40.486
Then he's wasting his time.

430
00:30:40.521 --> 00:30:43.146
That's what I keep telling him.

431
00:30:46.488 --> 00:30:49.730
If your girlfriend logged
that distress call.

432
00:30:49.873 --> 00:30:52.723
she's gonna be living
it down for a long time.

433
00:30:59.119 --> 00:31:00.617
I did it.

434
00:31:06.379 --> 00:31:08.345
I just couldn't shake it.

435
00:31:10.730 --> 00:31:13.729
I'd keep that to
myself if I were you.

436
00:31:19.443 --> 00:31:22.507
What's the good word. y'all?

437
00:31:22.679 --> 00:31:24.187
All right.

438
00:31:24.317 --> 00:31:27.136
How's my sweet old
rust bucket today?

439
00:31:27.308 --> 00:31:29.711
Well. I guess we'll find
out. won't we?

440
00:31:29.767 --> 00:31:31.223
I guess so.

441
00:31:33.226 --> 00:31:34.763
Okay.

442
00:31:38.291 --> 00:31:40.681
So just for the record. guys.

443
00:31:40.716 --> 00:31:42.302
I don't wanna be here right now.

444
00:31:42.364 --> 00:31:45.186
Me neither. But here we are.

445
00:31:45.233 --> 00:31:47.321
One big. happy unit.

446
00:31:47.463 --> 00:31:49.326
Knight. your flight plan is set.

447
00:31:49.391 --> 00:31:51.933
It'll be a two-hour trip to the
tango. flying tea-kettle.

448
00:31:52.001 --> 00:31:53.705
Thank you. Canterbury.

449
00:31:53.740 --> 00:31:56.343
Welcome. Knight. Godspeed.

450
00:31:56.378 --> 00:31:59.591
If you see anything that seems off.
you pack up the toys and come on home.

451
00:31:59.668 --> 00:32:01.329
No heroes. Captain.

452
00:32:01.394 --> 00:32:04.422
Clear to leave the barn.
Good luck.

453
00:32:33.348 --> 00:32:34.695
Really?

454
00:32:37.838 --> 00:32:39.571
She's off the clock.

455
00:32:40.080 --> 00:32:42.570
Then she can tell me that.

456
00:32:54.332 --> 00:32:55.976
I'd keep an eye on that guy.

457
00:32:56.011 --> 00:32:59.976
I hear he collects moon
rocks in his spare time.

458
00:33:00.164 --> 00:33:02.035
You wanna know what
else he's into?

459
00:33:02.070 --> 00:33:06.458
Hey. hey. now.
I'm just lookin' out for you.

460
00:33:07.810 --> 00:33:09.809
I need a woman's intuition.

461
00:33:11.346 --> 00:33:12.202
Who is she?

462
00:33:12.258 --> 00:33:15.336
Oh. she's just a
missing persons case

463
00:33:15.371 --> 00:33:18.129
I'm not "permitted to
discuss." you know.

464
00:33:19.233 --> 00:33:21.855
Juliette Andromeda Mao.

465
00:33:21.944 --> 00:33:24.716
She's the richest
bachelorette in the system.

466
00:33:25.514 --> 00:33:28.064
Now what would a rich girl do

467
00:33:28.349 --> 00:33:31.334
to really piss
Daddy off on Ceres?

468
00:33:31.392 --> 00:33:33.335
Are you asking what I did?

469
00:33:34.422 --> 00:33:37.191
Bang every space
bucker I could find.

470
00:33:37.843 --> 00:33:39.526
That's not helpful.

471
00:33:39.561 --> 00:33:42.301
Oh. I'm sorry. Miller.
Did you come here for my help?

472
00:33:42.336 --> 00:33:44.026
Come on.

473
00:33:44.464 --> 00:33:49.357
Admit it. You miss me.
You miss these little chats.

474
00:33:49.431 --> 00:33:51.749
Good night. Miller.

475
00:33:58.834 --> 00:34:01.921
Eat something. for God's sake.
You look like hell.

476
00:34:14.903 --> 00:34:17.917
_

477
00:34:21.074 --> 00:34:23.841
Config matches the
registry information.

478
00:34:24.915 --> 00:34:26.880
It's definitely the Scopuli.

479
00:34:27.071 --> 00:34:30.768
No IR or electro-mag other
than the distress beacon.

480
00:34:30.939 --> 00:34:32.257
Looks like the
reactor's shut down.

481
00:34:32.281 --> 00:34:34.513
but no radiation leakage.

482
00:34:35.759 --> 00:34:39.367
What about that thing that looks
like a big hole in the side?

483
00:34:39.954 --> 00:34:43.266
Uh. LADAR says it's a
big hole in the side.

484
00:34:45.921 --> 00:34:50.221
Well. the big array on the Cant's
reading no one within a million clicks.

485
00:34:50.256 --> 00:34:51.989
Looks like we're the
only game in town.

486
00:34:52.055 --> 00:34:55.019
Well. we came. we
looked. we. uh. left.

487
00:34:55.308 --> 00:34:57.835
No one's gonna know if we
set foot on that thing.

488
00:34:58.632 --> 00:35:00.549
_

489
00:35:01.078 --> 00:35:02.775
Take us in.

490
00:35:02.843 --> 00:35:05.924
And. Alex. if something
nasty's hiding in that ship.

491
00:35:05.959 --> 00:35:08.426
we bolt like hell and melt
anything behind us into slag.

492
00:35:08.461 --> 00:35:09.775
Good plan. Hoss.

493
00:35:09.810 --> 00:35:12.341
All right.
I'll go in and poke around.

494
00:35:14.369 --> 00:35:16.151
I'll go with him.

495
00:35:32.649 --> 00:35:34.478
Good times.

496
00:36:10.804 --> 00:36:13.768
How do you think that happened?

497
00:36:14.044 --> 00:36:17.862
It wasn't a torpedo.
A breaching charge did that.

498
00:36:23.018 --> 00:36:24.353
Amos.

499
00:36:25.477 --> 00:36:27.476
Keep that gun out.

500
00:36:29.280 --> 00:36:33.334
Engineering first.
I wanna know why that reactor's offline.

501
00:36:48.467 --> 00:36:51.465
Reactor wasn't
killed by the blast.

502
00:36:52.203 --> 00:36:54.973
Someone went through
the shutdown procedures.

503
00:36:56.494 --> 00:36:59.493
So. if everyone's dead.
who turned it off?

504
00:36:59.914 --> 00:37:02.879
Well. it wasn't pirates.

505
00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:05.247
They wouldn't have
left all that behind.

506
00:37:05.428 --> 00:37:08.103
And they left all the
pressure doors open.

507
00:37:11.066 --> 00:37:13.066
So no one could hide.

508
00:37:17.664 --> 00:37:18.958
Six o'clock!

509
00:37:22.404 --> 00:37:25.859
Naomi. Shed.
we need more eyes in here.

510
00:37:27.348 --> 00:37:29.347
All right.
Meet us on the bridge.

511
00:37:46.035 --> 00:37:47.516
Hey. guys?

512
00:37:48.979 --> 00:37:50.944
Where are all the bodies at?

513
00:37:51.501 --> 00:37:56.578
Amos. cut out the data core.
We'll take it with us.

514
00:37:56.623 --> 00:37:58.193
Roger that.

515
00:38:02.134 --> 00:38:04.797
These panels are all dead.

516
00:38:04.869 --> 00:38:08.394
How are they sending a distress
beacon with dead comms?

517
00:38:26.737 --> 00:38:28.289
Does that look like a...

518
00:38:28.384 --> 00:38:29.917
Well. maybe not...

519
00:38:29.975 --> 00:38:32.556
If it was a bomb. we'd be toast.

520
00:38:34.434 --> 00:38:36.433
It's a transmitter.

521
00:38:40.208 --> 00:38:42.810
This must be the
beacon that called us.

522
00:38:42.919 --> 00:38:44.716
Somebody planted it.

523
00:38:44.798 --> 00:38:46.797
Pirate bait.

524
00:38:47.273 --> 00:38:49.271
McDowell was right.

525
00:38:49.306 --> 00:38:53.796
Hoss. forwarding you an A-1
tight-beam from the Canterbury.

526
00:38:53.992 --> 00:38:57.381
Holden. a ship just
appeared near your location.

527
00:38:57.447 --> 00:39:01.206
How is that possible?
You cleared us out to a million clicks.

528
00:39:01.241 --> 00:39:03.553
It didn't show up on
any of our scopes.

529
00:39:03.588 --> 00:39:07.709
We're setting you a rendezvous point.
Get the hell back here.

530
00:39:18.165 --> 00:39:19.475
Alex! Disengage!

531
00:39:19.510 --> 00:39:20.980
My pleasure.

532
00:39:23.081 --> 00:39:24.838
Disengaging!

533
00:39:34.865 --> 00:39:36.194
Where did that thing come from?

534
00:39:36.229 --> 00:39:38.660
Damned if I know!
Just suddenly. it was there.

535
00:39:38.695 --> 00:39:40.289
Stealth tech. Has to be.

536
00:39:40.324 --> 00:39:42.323
Who the hell has
stealth like that?

537
00:39:43.840 --> 00:39:45.737
Mars.

538
00:39:58.984 --> 00:40:00.190
_

539
00:40:02.487 --> 00:40:04.428
That's more thinner to the
mix. all right?

540
00:40:04.463 --> 00:40:05.646
All right.

541
00:40:05.711 --> 00:40:08.029
Hey. hey.
you see that other one?

542
00:40:08.064 --> 00:40:10.643
- What was that?
- You got that other one with you?

543
00:40:11.656 --> 00:40:15.027
That's a cute kid. How old?

544
00:40:15.131 --> 00:40:16.637
Two and a half.

545
00:40:17.294 --> 00:40:18.490
Hi.

546
00:40:19.620 --> 00:40:21.605
How about you? Any kids?

547
00:40:23.081 --> 00:40:26.780
Yeah. no. I missed that boat.

548
00:40:50.404 --> 00:40:52.403
There you go. pal.

549
00:40:55.268 --> 00:40:57.268
My turn.

550
00:40:58.001 --> 00:41:00.169
My turn.

551
00:41:00.203 --> 00:41:02.919
Me turn. me turn!

552
00:41:12.414 --> 00:41:15.084
We had an understanding. Detective!
An arrangement!

553
00:41:15.119 --> 00:41:17.643
You can't just...
It was a mistake!

554
00:41:27.771 --> 00:41:31.008
You made your point.
I'm a changed man!

555
00:41:31.125 --> 00:41:33.114
Thank you for opening my eyes!

556
00:41:37.631 --> 00:41:39.269
Twice the money!

557
00:41:40.935 --> 00:41:42.910
I'll pay you double!

558
00:41:50.360 --> 00:41:53.082
Air is good. don't you think?

559
00:41:55.695 --> 00:41:57.693
Air is nice.

560
00:41:59.451 --> 00:42:02.152
Keep those filters
clean. asshole.

561
00:42:05.407 --> 00:42:06.788
Knight. we have your rendezvous.

562
00:42:06.823 --> 00:42:08.200
Negative. Unable.

563
00:42:08.289 --> 00:42:09.177
Advise.

564
00:42:09.212 --> 00:42:11.309
Bogey is 12.000
clicks and closing.

565
00:42:11.344 --> 00:42:13.127
Holden. advise!

566
00:42:16.271 --> 00:42:17.505
Torpedo launch!

567
00:42:17.540 --> 00:42:19.895
We're gonna take 'em for a ride.
Alex. go around the asteroid.

568
00:42:19.919 --> 00:42:22.836
Run 'em! Now!
Lead the torpedoes into the rock.

569
00:42:22.871 --> 00:42:25.674
What is your situation?
Please advise!

570
00:42:28.374 --> 00:42:30.285
Six thousand clicks.

571
00:42:30.851 --> 00:42:32.330
Five...

572
00:42:32.451 --> 00:42:34.063
Four...

573
00:42:34.574 --> 00:42:36.032
Three...

574
00:42:46.257 --> 00:42:48.039
Those weren't meant for us.

575
00:42:50.402 --> 00:42:53.088
Canterbury. burn like
hell. you've got incoming!

576
00:42:56.036 --> 00:42:59.059
Right 30. G-burn. Do it! Now!

577
00:42:59.169 --> 00:43:01.022
- Range?
- Two-four. Closing.

578
00:43:01.057 --> 00:43:02.377
Standby cargo door.

579
00:43:02.412 --> 00:43:03.904
Captain.
eject the ice as a shield.

580
00:43:03.939 --> 00:43:05.471
We're on it!
Stay off this channel.

581
00:43:05.506 --> 00:43:06.439
Ade?

582
00:43:06.474 --> 00:43:09.122
Ade. did Mac eject the ice?

583
00:43:09.157 --> 00:43:11.076
Did he eject the ice?

584
00:43:11.111 --> 00:43:13.923
You take a hit. you stay calm.
They just want the cargo.

585
00:43:13.958 --> 00:43:16.292
We'll SOS. start negotiations
for prisoner release. okay?

586
00:43:16.327 --> 00:43:17.251
- Just...
- Jim.

587
00:43:17.320 --> 00:43:19.762
There's something
you should know...

588
00:43:51.774 --> 00:43:53.411
She's gone.

589
00:44:04.721 --> 00:44:06.166
They nuked her.

590
00:44:08.891 --> 00:44:10.449
She's gone.

591
00:44:19.575 --> 00:44:24.572
Sync and corrections by
explosiveskull www.addic7ed.com

591
00:44:25.305 --> 00:45:25.418
